{{Orphan|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox artwork | title = Holoscenes | wikidata = | image = File:Holoscenes performs in the Surfers Paradise, Queensland during 2018 Commonwealth Games, 02.jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = Holoscenes performs in the Surfers Paradise, Queensland during 2018 Commonwealth Games | artist = [[Lars Jan]] | year = 21st century<!-- If after 1583 CE, use {{start date|YYYY}} --> | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | catalogue = | medium = [[Installation art]] | movement = | subject = [[Climate change]] | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | website = http://earlymorningopera.com/wp/projects/holoscenes/ }}
'''''Holoscenes''''' is a multi-format work of [[installation art]] by [[Los Angeles]] artist [[Lars Jan]].
==Description== ''Holoscenes,'' features a single totemic, aquarium-like sculpture sited in public space, standing thirteen feet tall and viewable from 360 degrees. <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://earlymorningopera.com/wp/projects/holoscenes/|title=HOLOSCENES|work=Early Morning Opera|access-date=2018-05-12|language=en-US}}</ref>
In an [[allegory]] of the rising [[sea level]]s produced by [[climate change]],<ref name="Alvarez">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/12/05/us/water-as-a-climate-change-gut-punch-in-a-city-defined-by-an-ocean.html?_r=0|title=Water as a Climate-Change Gut Punch in a City Defined by an Ocean|last1=Alvarez|first1=Lizette|date=4 December 2015|work=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=8 December 2015}}</ref> the aquarium is animated by a powerful custom hydraulic system that pumps up to 15 tons of water in and out in less than a minute, creating a series of mini-floods to which the performers must adapt. Over the course of several hours, a series of performers play variously the guitar, sell fruit, don an [[abaya]], uncoil a garden hose, and perform other familiar tasks as the water rises and falls around each in turn.<ref name="ArtburstMiami">{{cite news|title=MDC Live Arts' 'Holoscenes' Explores Life Underwater|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/arts/mdc-live-arts-holoscenes-explores-life-underwater-8083268|access-date=8 December 2015| work = [[Miami New Times]] |date=30 November 2015}}</ref>
==Exhibitions== The piece has been shown/performed during The [[2018 Commonwealth Games|Commonwealth Games]] Festival 2018, Australia (2018); <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gc2018.com/event/holoscenes-lars-jan-early-morning-opera-usa|title=Holoscenes {{!}} Lars Jan / Early Morning Opera (USA) {{!}} Gold Coast 2018 Commonwealth Games|website=Gold Coast 2018|language=en|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref> Times Square Arts & [[World Science Festival]], New York (2017);<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://arts.timessquarenyc.org/times-square-arts/projects/at-the-crossroads/holoscenes/index.aspx|title=Times Square Arts: Holoscenes|website=arts.timessquarenyc.org|language=en|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref> Art Abu Dhabi [[New York University Abu Dhabi|NYU Abu Dhabi]], UAE (2016);<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nyuad-artscenter.org/en_US/events/2016/holoscenes/|title=HOLOSCENES — NYUAD Arts Center|website=NYUAD Arts Center|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-12}}</ref> London's Burning Festival (2016); [[Art Basel|Art Basel, Miami Beach]] (2015); at the [[John and Mable Ringling Museum of Art|John and Mable Ringing Museum]], Sarasota (2015); [[Nuit Blanche]], [[Toronto]] (2014);<ref name=AndrewGee>{{cite news|last1=Andrew-Gee|first1=Eric|title=Toronto’s Nuit Blanche 2014 brings out art lovers, street partiers alike|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2014/10/04/torontos_nuit_blanche_2014_brings_out_art_lovers_street_partiers_alike.html|access-date=8 December 2015| work = [[Toronto Star]]|date=4 October 2014}}</ref> and at the [[Pasadena Museum of California Art]] (2015).<ref name=Schroeder>{{cite news|last1=Schroeder|first1=Amy Newlove|title=Artist Lars Jan Puts the Life Aquatic on Display|url=http://www.lamag.com/culturefiles/life-aquatic-wet-work-performance-artist-lars-jan/|access-date=8 December 2015| work = [[Los Angeles (magazine)|Los Angeles]] |date=27 January 2015}}</ref><ref name=Gelt>{{cite news|last1=Gelt|first1=Jessica|title=Floodwaters Make Statement in 'Holoscenes' at Museum of California Art|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-lars-jan-holoscenes-20150218-story.html|access-date=8 December 2015| work = [[Los Angeles Times]] |date=18 February 2015}}</ref>
