==Literary works==
Before recognized internationally as a novelist, Meja Mwangi worked as a soundman at French television ORTF,<ref name=idloc>{{cite web|url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n50027673|title=soundman for French Broadcasting Corp., Nairobi|access-date=2016-10-26}}</ref> when he started writing his first novel.<ref name=killme>{{cite book|url=|title=Kill Me Quick|publisher=East African Ecucational Publishers|page=backmatter|year=1973}}</ref> His literal works were issued and read by limited readers in Kenya and African nations until translation in French, German, and English began in the 1980s when he had put several novels in print already.

