==Interviews==

"Interviews on [[Voice of America]]" was recorded between 1975-1979, and broadcast preservation master was archived for Library of Congress Magnetic Recording Laboratory in 1977.<ref name=voa>{{cite film|url=https://catalog.loc.gov/vwebv/search?searchCode=STNO&searchArg=96703614&searchType=1&recCount=10
|title=Meja Mwangi of Kenya|type=Full sound recording|series=Archive of World Literature on Tape, between 1975-1979|work=Conversations with African writers (Radio program)|format=1 sound tape reel (30 min.) analog, 7 1/2 ips, 2 track, mono; 7 in|people=Meja Mwangi, Lee Nichols (Interviewer)|location=Washington, D.C., USA|publisher=Voice of America (Organization)||lccn=96703614|year=1977}}</ref>{{refn|name=VoA|group=note|Additional formats, Washington, D.C.: 1 sound tape reel : analog, 7 1/2 ips, 2 track, mono. ; 10 in. Unedited version -- preservation master. Washington, D.C. : Library of Congress Magnetic Recording Laboratory, 1979. On 1 sound tape reel: analog, 7 1/2 ips, 2 track, mono.}} It was in 1979 when the unedited version of audio recording was copied from tapes lent by  Lee Nichols, the interviewer of the program, which was archived at the Library of Congress. The transcript of broadcast version was produced around 1977.<ref name=transcript>{{cite book|title=Conversations with African writers|pages=195–205|author=Voice of America|publisher=|location=Washington, D.C.|year=1981}}</ref>
Bernth Lindfor interviewed twenty-seven writers from six African countries including Meja Mwangi. Lindfor was a prominent scholar of Africana, and he archived in his library the four magazines that published those interviews. Lindfor reprinted them, or ''Palaver'',<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://palaverjournal.com|title=Palaver|publisher=UNCW's online interdisciplinary journal|access-date=2016-10-26}}</ref> ''Dem-Say'', ''Mazungumzo'', and ''Kulankula''.<ref name=highbeam>{{cite web|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc|title=Africa Talks Back: Interviews with Anglo-phone African Authors — Book Review) |access-date=2016-10-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Interviews with Anglo-phone African Authors — Book Review|series=Africa Talks Back|work=World Literature Today|last=Roger|first= Kurtz, J |editor= Lindfors, Bernth |location=Asmara, Eritrea|publisher=Africa World Press|isbn=086543-965-6|date=2003-04-01}}</ref>

