'''''Symphony of Monody''''' is a 2005 composition by the [[Persian people|Persian]] [[composer]] [[Mehdi Hosseini]] performed and recorded in Saint Petersburg, 3 Jun 2007, by the [[Saint Petersburg Academic Symphony Orchestra]] and conducted by Daniel Black.<ref>[http://www.tehrantimes.com/index_View.asp?code=196271 Tehran Times]</ref> The work is based on folk music material of [[Lorestan]].<ref>reMusik.org | [http://mehdihosseini.net/symphony-of-monody/ Saint-Petersburg Contemporary Music Resource Center.] Article by ''Timothy Dunne''</ref>

